{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pulls/84", "id": 1295525938, "node_id": "PR_kwDOIRJeAc5NOCgy", "html_url": "https://github.com/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pull/84", "diff_url": "https://github.com/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pull/84.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pull/84.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/issues/84", "number": 84, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "switch tunnel_ext to tokio::io::copy_bidirectional", "user": {"login": "bobzilladev", "id": 2207276, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMDcyNzY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2207276?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev", "html_url": "https://github.com/bobzilladev", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bobzilladev/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Ran into an issue working with Django autoreloader. Django would close down its half of the connection on reload, but the next http request coming in over the tunnel would block. Traced it to the tunnel_ext which is doing a `join` on both sides. One side breaks out of its byte-shoveling loop but the other one keeps going, its write succeeded and there's nothing to read, so it never breaks and sends a FIN. Switching it to a [copy_bidirectional](https://docs.rs/tokio/latest/tokio/io/fn.copy_bidirectional.html) like this takes care of the issue.\r\n\r\n_Previous description:_\r\n\r\nSwitching it to a `select` like this takes care of the issue, one future completes and drop's/muxado tears down the other side.\r\n\r\nIs there a downside to moving to something like this? Thought about waiting on the other side for a short time to let it try and make more progress in case of a unidirectional issue. Probably unlikely?\r\n\r\nAlso don't know if this is how you'd want it implemented, `tokio` looks to have its own `select`, but this change uses `futures` like the `join` did.", "created_at": "2023-03-30T02:34:00Z", "updated_at": "2023-03-30T19:36:39Z", "closed_at": "2023-03-30T19:36:38Z", "merged_at": "2023-03-30T19:36:38Z", "merge_commit_sha": "564e4cf175724aced0d04bb26b2172e891aae128", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pulls/84/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pulls/84/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/issues/84/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ngrok/ngrok-rust/statuses/52bebfb35b3451ffd374f863f6fac92cc62abf7b", "head": {"label": "ngrok:bob/select", "ref": "bob/select", "sha": "52bebfb35b3451ffd374f863f6fac92cc62abf7b", "user": {"login": "ngrok", "id": 10625446, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwNjI1NDQ2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10625446?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ngrok", "html_url": "https://github.com/ngrok", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ngrok/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ngrok/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ngrok/gists{/gist_id}", "star